*   [Guató language](/Guat%C3%B3_language). ISO 639-3 code. Spoken in Brazil. Another one. Fading. Like everything else.

## Places

Where things are. Or aren't.

*   [Goleta station](/Goleta_station), California, U.S. Station code: GTA. A place to wait. For trains that might never come.
*   [Gorkhaland Territorial Administration](/Gorkhaland_Territorial_Administration). A semi-autonomous region. In India. A bit of order, maybe. Or just a different kind of chaos.
*   [Grande Traversée des Alpes](/Grande_Travers%C3%A9e_des_Alpes). A hiking trail. In France. Across the Alps. A long walk. To nowhere in particular.
*   [Grande Traversata delle Alpi](/Grande_Traversata_delle_Alpi). Another hiking trail. In Italy. Also the Alps. Are we walking in circles?
*   [Great Ayton railway station](/Great_Ayton_railway_station), England. Station code: GTA. More waiting. More trains. More dust.
*   [Greater Tokyo Area](/Greater_Tokyo_Area). A metropolitan area. In Japan. So many people. So much noise. So much loneliness.
*   [Greater Toronto Area](/Greater_Toronto_Area). A metropolitan area. Southern Ontario, Canada. More of the same. Just colder.

## Science and Technology

Where we try to control things. And fail.

*   [Gas tungsten arc welding](/Gas_tungsten_arc_welding). A process. Joining metal. With heat. A controlled burn.
*   [Gene transfer agent](/Gene_transfer_agent). A DNA-containing particle. Produced by bacteria. Tiny things. With big plans.
*   [Global Technology Associates](/Global_Technology_Associates). An Internet firewall maker. Trying to keep the bad out. Like putting up a flimsy fence against a tidal wave.
*   GTA. A codon for the amino acid [valine](/Valine). The building blocks of… us. Even the code has its own language.
*   [GTA Teleguam](/GTA_Teleguam). A telecommunications company. In Guam. Connecting people. Across vast, empty oceans.

## Vehicles

Things that move. Or pretend to.

### Alfa Romeo

*   [Alfa Romeo GTA](/Alfa_Romeo_GTA). A succession of Italian sport coupés. 1965–1975. Based on the Giulia. Sleek. Dangerous.
*   147 GTA. A high-performance version. Of the [Alfa Romeo 147](/Alfa_Romeo_147). Faster. More aggressive.
*   156 GTA. A high-performance version. Of the [Alfa Romeo 156](/Alfa_Romeo_156). More of the same. Just… more.
*   MiTo GTA. A concept version. Of the [Alfa Romeo MiTo](/Alfa_Romeo_MiTo). A dream. That never quite materialized.

